The paper proposes a new graph neural network architecture that is based solely on the attention mechanism and does not rely on graph convolution or aggregation operators. This makes it relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on learning graph representations using a neural network architecture.
